    "overview_number": 2,
    "overview_title": "Copycats",
    "overview_subtitle": "Constructing a Regular Hexagon Inscribed in a Circle",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students use construction tools to duplicate line segments and angles. They use these constructions to create angles twice the measure of a given angle and line segments twice the length of a given line segment. They then use that they know about line segment duplication to construct a regular hexagon inscribed in a circle. Students use angle duplication to verify the Inscribed Angle Theorem."
  },
